caption:
FBI and New Orleans law enforcement don't believe there were any other suspects involved in the Bourbon Street attack that caused 14 deaths, and injured dozens on New Year's Day. ⁠
⁠
"We do not assess at this point that anyone else is involved in this attack except for Shamsud-Din Jabbar," said Christopher Raia, the deputy assistant director of the FBI's counter-terrorism division, during a Thursday news conference. ⁠
